<!--
  IL2CPP managed-code stripping preservation for the RTMPE SDK runtime.

  The SDK locates [RtmpeRpc] handlers and [NetworkVariable] members by
  reflection and invokes them through MethodInfo.Invoke. The stripper cannot
  prove those members are reachable from a static call site, so on an AOT
  (iOS / IL2CPP) build it would remove them and the corresponding RPCs and
  replicated variables would silently stop firing on device. Preserving the
  runtime assembly keeps that reflective surface intact.

  Game-side [RtmpeRpc] methods and custom NetworkVariable<T> closed types live
  in the consumer's own assembly and must be preserved there as well — see
  Documentation~/troubleshooting.md ("IL2CPP").
-->
<linker>
    <assembly fullname="RTMPE.SDK.Runtime" preserve="all" />
</linker>
